quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  13,6,"They challenge you to hasten the coming of evil upon them before the coming of any good, although people who followed a like course before had met with exemplary punishment (from Allah). Verily your Lord is forgiving to mankind despite all their wrong-doing. Verily your Lord is also severe in retribution.",footnotes:178520:1
  13,7,"Those who refused to believe in you say: "Why has no (miraculous) sign been sent down upon him from his Lord?" You are only a warner, and every people has its guide.",footnotes:178521:1,footnotes:178522:2
  13,8,"Allah knows what every female bears; and what the wombs fall short of (in gestation), and what they may add. With Him everything is in a fixed measure.",footnotes:178523:1
  13,9,"He knows both what is hidden and what is manifest. He is the Supreme One, the Most High."
  13,10,"It is all the same for Him whether any of you says a thing secretly, or says it loudly, and whether one hides oneself in the darkness of night, or struts about in broad daylight."